Set Up Data Aggregation for Segment Intelligence

To use the Segment Intelligence app and gain insights on aggregated data, select the data model objects for data aggregation and the segment attributes.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience	Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To manage Data Cloud:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
To set up data aggregation for Segment Intelligence:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
1. Select the Data Model Objects for Aggregation

The setup process suggests data model objects (DMO). You can use the suggested DMOs or select a different one.

In Segment Intelligence setup, under Data Aggregation, go to Select DMOs for Data Aggregation, and click Select.
Select the Unified Individual DMO. The Unified Individual DMO contains the unified records for each individual.
Select the Unified Link Individual DMO.
The Unified Individual Link DMO links between the unified records and the records that created them. See Unified Individual. 
Click Next.
(Optional) Select the Unified Individual Extension DMOs.
These Unified Individual Extension DMOs are included. See Individual Object Data Modeling Requirements.
Unified Individual Contact Point Address—The record of the contact’s home address.
Unified Individual Contact Point Email—The record of the contact’s email address.
Unified Individual Contact Point Phone—The record of the contact’s phone number.
Click Next.
Select the Segment Membership DMO.
These Segment Memberships are included. See Segment Membership Data Model Object.
Unified Individual Latest—The current Segment Membership status.
Unified Individual History—Contains the Segment Membership change log.
Click Next.
Select the standard DMOs.
These DMOs are included. See Engagement Data Model and Sales Order Data Model.
Email Engagement—Contains all the email engagement events.
Engagement Topic—Contains the engagement topic events.
Market Journey Activity—Contains the Journey activity events.
Market Segment—Contains the market segment information.
Click Next.
Select the Marketing Cloud Engagement DMOs.
These Engagement DMOs are included. See Marketing Cloud Engagement Data Bundle Information.
Campaign—Contains the Engagement campaign data.
Market Journey—Contains Engagement journey data.
Click Finish.
2. Select Attributes for Segmentation
On the Segment Intelligence setup page, go to Data Aggregation.
Under Select Segment Attributes, click Select.
Select at least two attributes.
Save your changes.
3. Aggregate Your Data for Segment Intelligence

Aggregate your first and third-party data. Only aggregated data is displayed in Segment Intelligence dashboards.

On the Segment Intelligence setup page, go to Data Aggregation.
Under Aggregate Your Data, click Aggregate.
These DLOs and DMOs are created automatically for storing your aggregated data.
DLOS	DMOS
Segint No Property Aggregation	Segint Unified Aggregation
Segint One Property Aggregation	Segint One Property Aggregation
Segint Two Property Aggregation	Segint Two Property Aggregation
Segint Third-Party Aggregation	Segint Segment Aggregation
Segint Segment Aggregation	

Your first and third-party data is aggregated and inserted into the DLOs. The aggregated data includes up to 30 days of first-party data and up to 30 days of third-party data. After the aggregation is complete, the data is visible in the Segment Intelligence dashboard.
